Cosatu president Zingiswa Losi delivers the Workers Day address as some people return to work under lockdown #Level4. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cosatu president, Zingiswa Losi, has lauded all health workers as heroes during her Workers' Day address. This is the first time that a Workers Day address is done without crowds of people at a rally. She said South Africans continue to live in poverty facing inequality and exploitation, 26 years into democracy. READ: South Africa enters into level 4 lockdown Losi also encouraged employers to protect their workers. The country is currently under a level four lockdown. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.